cov:req1-2026-07-02T15-36-56 a dqv:QualityMeasurement ;
    dqv:computedOn <https://w3id.org/aidoc-ap/1.0> ;
    dqv:isMeasurementOf cov:annexCoverageMetric ;
    dqv:value 0.95 ;
    prov:wasAttributedTo <https://w3id.org/aidoc-ap/alignment#LLMCoverageBot> ;
    prov:wasGeneratedBy <https://w3id.org/aidoc-ap/coverage/llm-run/2026-07-02T15-36-56> ;
    cov:forRequirement aiact:req1 ;
    cov:matchedTerm aidoc:AIProvider,
        aidoc:AISystem,
        aidoc:ChangeLog,
        aidoc:DataSheet,
        aidoc:DeclarationOfConformity,
        aidoc:ModelVersioning,
        aidoc:intendedPurpose,
        aidoc:version ;
    cov:missingLabel "AI System Lineage",
        "Release Notes" ;
    cov:reasoning "The ontology directly addresses all aspects of the requirement. 'AI System' represents the system itself, 'AI Provider' identifies the provider, and 'version' captures version information. 'Model Versioning' and 'Change Log' provide details on relation to previous versions. 'intended purpose' is a direct property. 'Data Sheet' can contain high-level descriptions of the AI system and its intended use, while 'Declaration of Conformity' implies documentation about the system’s characteristics."@en .

